Explanation: According to the documents, the British Oceanographic Data Centre (BODC) was initially located at the National Institute of Oceanography, Wormley in Surrey, and later transferred to Bidston Observatory on the Wirral, near Liverpool. However, by the time of the most recent document (2019), it appears that the NOC (which includes BODC) has moved its operations to independent & charitable status, but still references being located in Liverpool. Therefore, the statement "The British Oceanographic Data Centre is located in Liverpool" can be considered supported by the documents.
